channel.title: Everytime I use a proxy, I can never login to anything! :(
channel.description:
I keep getting this error no matter what proxy I use.
You are trying to use a node of the CoDeeN CDN Network. Your IP address is not recognized as a valid PlanetLab address, so your access to CoDeeN does not include all HTTP types
And I always get that error when I try to login to a website. Such as this website, or yahoo email, or gmail, or anything that requires a login when I'm proxying. Does anyone know a proxy or list of proxies that actually let you login to websites? The proxy list that I have used is this one. http://www.samair.ru/proxy/proxy-17.htm and a few others I found on google.
